# {{context|physics|lang=en}} An interaction between a [[polarize]]d electromagnetic pulse, such as a beam of light, and a [[magnetic field]], in which the plane of polarization is rotated in proportion to the [[intensity]] of the component of the magnetic field in the direction of travel of the pulse.

